												<p>Dagomar Degroot is Associate Professor of Environmental History at Georgetown University. A contributor to the <em>Washington Post</em>, <em>Nature</em>, and <em>Aeon</em>, he is the author of <em>The Frigid Golden Age: Climate Change, the Little Ice Age, and the Dutch Republic, 1560â€“1720</em>, named one of the ten best history books of 2018 by the <em>Financial Times</em>.</p>
